SIMPLE: pubes
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pubes
<hw>Pu"bes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the hair which
appears on the body at puberty, from <ets>pubes</ets> adult.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The hair which appears
upon the lower part of the hypogastric region at the age of
puberty.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Hence (as more commonly used), the
lower part of the hypogastric region; the pubic region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The down of plants; a downy or
villous substance which grows on plants; pubescence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pubescence</ent>⟦br⟧
